Parliament, Thursday, 14 November 2019 – The Standing and Select Committees on Appropriation will tomorrow hold public hearings on the Division of Revenue Amendment Bill [B15 – 2019]. The Bill proposes to amend the Division of Revenue Act, 2019 (Act No. 16 of 2019), in accordance with section 12(4) of the Money Bills and Related Matters Act, 2009 (Act No. 9 of 2009), since the national adjustments budget for the 2019/20 financial year necessitates changes to the Division of Revenue Act, 2019. The committees will also be briefed on the Bill by the South African Local Government Association. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Friday, 14 November 2019
	Time: 09:00 am 
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MR SFISO BUTHELEZI AND MS DIKELEDI MAHLANGU. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za The room in which a House meets to debate is called a “Chamber”.Read more